&lt;p&gt;Paying for an independent school education is a significant investment.&amp;nbsp; Although affordability can be an issue, it may be helpful to explore independent school as one of your child&amp;rsquo;s options and particularly to learn how these schools can support families to bring tuition costs closer to meeting their financial needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Know what to expect as you travel though the process, how to separate fact from fiction, and how to leverage the help and supports that are available to you.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Presenter: Mark J. Mitchell, Vice President, Access &amp;amp; Affordability at National Association of Independent Schools (NAIS), supports the work of K-12 schools and other organizations in the effective administration of financial aid programs. Mark regularly presents on tuition pricing, affordability, demographic and income trends, and school financial aid management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

